G. Patr. Καλητορίδης
                    83, Il. 13.478;
                    s. Aeneas Il. 13.541.

A comrade of Odysseus in his ship. Killed by mishap at Circe's house Od. 10.552; his shade begs for funeral rites
                        Od. 11.51, 57;
                    the funeral Od. 12.10.

Patr. Ἰησονίδης Son of Ieson and Hypsipyle.
                    Sent wine to the Greeks from Lemnos Il. 6.468;
                    purchased Lycaon-2 Il. 21.41, Il. 23.747.

(περίφρων, φίλη τροφός). Odysseus's nurse,
                    daughter of Ops. Puts Telemachus to 
 bed Od. 1.429; in charge of the store-room Od. 2.347, T. bids her prepare provisions for his
                    voyage 348; she encloses the maids while
                    Odysseus and T. remove the arms Od. 19.15;
                    washes O. Od. 19.357, recognizes his scar 392, 467;
                    encloses the maids before the fight Od. 21.380;
                    enumerates the unfaithful maids Od. 22.419;
                    brings sulphur Od. 22.480; tells Penelope of
                    O.'s return and the slaughter of the suitors Od.
                        23.1; etc.

(μέγας). Father of Iphitus-2. The ruler of
                    Oechalia Il. 2.596, 730: skilled with the bow Od. 8.224;
                    challenged Apollo to a contest with the bow and was slain by him Od. 8.226; left his bow to his son Od. 21.32.

(ι), called also Λευκοθέη (καλλίσφυρος).
                    Daughter of Cadmus. Made immortal Od. 5.334;
                    comes to the aid of Odysseus when his raft is shattered Od. 5.333, 461.

Son of Alectryon. A leader of the Boeotians Il.
                        2.494; slays Phylacus-1 Il. 7.35;
                        Il. 13.91; wounded by Hector Il. 17.601, 605.

(ἀτάλαντος Ἄρηϊ, δουρικλυτός). Patr. Φυλεΐδης. Son of Phyleus and leader of the men of
                    Doulichium and the Echinean Islands Il. 2.627;
                    slays Pedaeus Il. 5.69; leading the Epeians Il. 13.692; Il.
                        15.302; slays Croesmus Il. 15.520;
                        Il. 15.535; slays Amphiclus Il. 16.313; Il.
                        19.239.

(δῖος, μεγάθυμος, πλήξιππος). Son of Peteos
                    and leader of the Athenians Il. 2.552, Il. 4.327; in charge of part of the wall Il. 12.331, 373;
                        Il. 13.195, 690, Il. 15.331.
